class MyCalendarThree {
    private TreeMap<Integer, Integer> delta;

    public MyCalendarThree() {
        delta = new TreeMap<>();
    }

    public int book(int startTime, int endTime) {
        delta.put(startTime, delta.getOrDefault(startTime, 0) + 1);
        delta.put(endTime, delta.getOrDefault(endTime, 0) - 1);

        int active = 0, max = 0;
        for (int d : delta.values()) {
            active += d;
            max = Math.max(max, active);
        }
        return max;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n log n) per book
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses a TreeMap to store start/end events as ±1 deltas; each book inserts two keys and scans the sorted map once to compute the running maximum overlap. Simple, cache-friendly, and optimal for the given constraints.

